# make sure we're in the context we want
Context("Numeric");

$space=random(1,2,1)*random(1,2,1)*random(1,2,1);
$a1=random(1,5,1);
$a2=random(1,5,1);
$q1=$a1*100;
$q2=$a2*100;

$an1=$a1*29+$a2*18;
$an2=$a1*3+$a2*25;
$an3=$a1*4+$a2*6;



TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ textbook_ref_exact("Holt Linear Algebra", "2.1","33") \} 
$PAR
Fertilizer is sold in 100 pound bags labelled with the amount of nitrogen ( N), phosphoric acid ( P2O5), and potash ( K2O) present. The mixture of these nutrients varies from one type of fertilizer to the next. 
$PAR
For example, a \(100\) pound bag of Vigoro Ultra Turf fertilizer contains \(29\) pounds of nitrogen, \(3\) pounds of phosphoric acid, and \(4\) pounds of potash. 
$PAR
Another type of fertilizer, Parker’s Premium Starter, has \(18\) pounds of nitrogen, \(25\) pounds of phosphoric acid, and \(6\) pounds of potash per \(100\) pounds. 
$PAR
Determine the amount of each type required to yield a mixture containing the \($an1\) pounds of nitrogen, \($an2\) pounds of phosphoric acid, and \($an2\) pounds of potash.
$PAR
The mixture contains \{ans_rule(10)\} pounds of Vigoro, and \{ans_rule(10)\} pounds of Parker’s.

$PAR



END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

ANS(num_cmp($q1));
ANS(num_cmp($q2));

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR 
SOLUTION 
$PAR
$PAR
Use row reduction to solve
\[(x_1)
\left[\begin{matrix} 29 \cr 3 \cr 4 \cr \end{matrix}\right]+
(x_2)
\left[\begin{matrix} 18 \cr 25 \cr 6 \cr \end{matrix}\right]=
\left[\begin{matrix} $an1 \cr $an2 \cr $an3 \cr \end{matrix}\right]
\]
$PAR
We see \(x_1=$a1\) and \(x_2=$a2\), so we need \($q1\) pounds of Vigoro and\($q2\) pounds of Parker's.
$PAR
$PAR

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

